# Mission plan

**Execution model:** Squad Leader orchestrates stages on separate agent lanes. Stage I (**debug-and-fix**) is always spawned. After a verified fix, the developer picks **code promotion** (**§5 planning child**: inline **`new-plan`** → **`pr-plan`**, then that lane runs **`pr-plan` §5c–§5d** and spawns **`coding-session`**), **Ad-Hoc PRD only**, or **findings report only**. **Forbidden:** Squad Leader **`mission_control_spawn_agent`** for **`coding-session`**. When the fix is not verified or blocked, the Squad Leader produces a **Debug session findings report** before dispatch resolution. Reuse plan-and-deliver planning and ship skills; do not duplicate ship-chain steps in this mission.

## Objectives

1. **Log-first diagnosis** — Bootstrap a debug worktree, prioritize log access and debug instrumentation before substantive code analysis.
2. **Fix loop** — Propose fixes with test scenarios; apply on developer approval; run automated tests and guided manual verification; loop on failure until fixed or blocked.
3. **Post-fix routing** — After a verified fix (or abandon), the developer confirms the exit on the debug child lane (step 7); under Checkpoint trust the **Squad Leader** treats that confirmation as **auto-approval** and routes per **`exitRecommendation`** / **`abandonMission`** without repeating §4:
   - **Code promotion** — spawn a §5 planning child (**`new-plan`** plus inline **`pr-plan`**); **that planning lane** runs **`pr-plan` §5c–§5d** and spawns **`coding-session`** on the debug worktree (Squad Leader does **not** emit the §5d spawn), so deploy tests and additional written tests have a PR plan to update.
   - **Ad-Hoc PRD only** — spawn **`ad-hoc-prd`** to capture fix context without starting code promotion.
   - **Findings report only** — no planning, no **`coding-session`**; Squad Leader produces a **Debug session findings report** from child outputs.
4. **Reuse plan-and-deliver** — Downstream delivery delegates to existing R&D skills; this mission owns debug orchestration only.

