### 5. Create PR plan anchor (spawned planning handoff — code-promotion path only)

- `type`: Agent engagement and handover.
- `execution`: spawned.
- `intent`: Create the PR plan anchor required before code promotion, so `coding-session` receives `targetPlanPath` and can update deploy-test and written-test sections during ship.
- `target agent role`: Debug promotion planning agent (plan-and-deliver).
- `assigned skill`: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/new-plan/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/new-plan/SKILL.md), followed by **`pr-plan`** population per [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-plan/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-plan/SKILL.md).
- `inputs`: `mode: "standalone"`, `requestedPlanKind: "pr-plan"`, `upstreamSkill: "debug-and-fix"` from Mission Control, and a debug handover seed containing child `outputs.fixSummary`, `outputs.testEvidence`, `outputs.worktreePath`, `outputs.worktreeName`, and `outputs.hostingRoot`. Root plan parent is resolved inside **`new-plan`** (sidecar **`parent: null`**) — **`new-plan`** frontmatter has no `parent` spawn key. When this step spawns a skill whose frontmatter declares **`parent`** as **`type: string`** (for example **`master-planner`** on other paths), emit **`"parent": "null"`** in spawn JSON for standalone root plans — **never** JSON `null`. See **`plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** § *Universal spawn preflight* row **1b**.
- `spawn run-request fields`: `inputs`, `warmUpRules` per target skill frontmatter, `laneRules` when required by the planning skill manifest, and `initiatingPrompt` with debug handover plus the approved post-fix exit — **must** state that this planning lane owns **`pr-plan` §5c–§5d** (spawn **`coding-session`** with existing debug `worktreePath` / `worktreeName`, `developerApprovedImplementation: true`, and the §5 deploy-plan Before/After binding); **forbidden** to tell the child to skip §5d or redirect spawn to the Squad Leader.
- **Worktree ownership handoff (binding):** The §3 debug child that ran center **`worktree-setup.sh`** and MCP **`sedea_add_worktree_folder`** for absolute **`outputs.worktreePath`** **passes cleanup ownership** of that path to the §5 planning child with the seed. Path/name alone is **not** enough — **`initiatingPrompt`** and **`inputs`** **must** state that the planning lane **inherits** worktree ownership for that exact absolute path (including that MCP mount already ran when **`sedea_add_worktree_folder`** succeeded on the debug lane). The planning child **must** forward that inheritance on **`pr-plan` §5d** to **`coding-session`** (see §5b). **Forbidden:** implying the planning child or **`coding-session`** must re-run setup to “own” the path, or that remount-only reuse makes ownership unclear.
- `pr-plan standalone exception`: Debug fixes do not necessarily originate from an approved parent **`### PR list`**. This mission explicitly permits a standalone **`pr-plan`** population handoff after **`new-plan`** creates the target plan; the handoff must pass `targetPlanPath`, `targetPlanSlug`, and the debug handover seed. If **`pr-plan`** cannot populate without parent topology, stop and use structured choice to revise the plan anchor, create the missing parent planning context, or switch exits — do not spawn **`coding-session`** without a PR plan.
- **§7 Deploy test plan seeding (binding — `upstreamSkill: debug-and-fix`):** When **`pr-plan`** drafts the PR plan **`## N. Deploy test plan`** from the debug handover seed, treat manual scenarios already verified in the debug session (`outputs.testEvidence` / approved manual gates) as **already covered pre-promotion**:
  - **`### Local test`** — omit those manual scenarios as deploy-walk manual steps. Prefer agent-executable checks only (scripts, automated verify, standing pre-review bar). When no PR-specific agent-executable Local test items remain, use the empty-section form (*None — manual checks covered in debug session; agent-executable / standing pre-review only.*) rather than re-listing debug manual scenarios.
  - **`### Production`** — list those same debug-verified manual scenarios as **post-merge retests** (plus any production-only checks). Do **not** drop them from the plan entirely.
  - **Forbidden:** copying debug-session manual test gates unchanged into Local test so **`coding-session`** / **`deploy-walk`** re-run them as pre-PR manual waits.
- `expected output`: Child terminal or aggregate output with `outputs.targetPlanPath`, `outputs.targetPlanSlug`, `outputs.readyForImplementation: true`, optional `outputs.implementationHandoffStatus` / `outputs.spawnCorrelationId` / ship fields after **`pr-plan` §5d–§5e**, and any `outputs.remainingTasks` from **`new-plan`** / **`pr-plan`**.
- `next-step resolution`: After spawn, the planning child continues through **`pr-plan` handoff + §5d** **`coding-session`** spawn; Squad Leader enters §5b **oversight wait** (**#external-wait**) — **ack only**, do **not** emit a leader **`coding-session`** spawn when §5 resume reports ready. If the planning child reports unresolved plan target, missing parent topology that blocks standalone population, approval gaps, or terminates without §5d and without explicit defer, USER_CHECKPOINT gate below.
- **Agent session closure** and **Dispatch resolution**: Same as step 3 — emit spawn → **#external-wait** before turn end; child terminal only; Squad Leader continues protocol.

USER_CHECKPOINT — revise planning anchor, retry, or switch exits when PR plan creation is blocked.

### 5b. Code promotion oversight (Squad Leader)

- `type`: Branching logic (oversight wait — not a Squad Leader spawn).
- `execution`: none on leader — detached **`coding-session`** is spawned by the §5 planning child via **`pr-plan` §5d**.
- `intent`: Track the detached **`coding-session`** ship chain (already-modified debug worktree) after the §5 planning child creates the PR plan and emits §5d; resume on bubbled child terminals.
- `target agent role`: Coding session agent (plan-and-deliver) — **owned by §5 planning child spawn**, not the Squad Leader.
- `assigned skill`: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md) (spawn contract consumed by **`pr-plan` §5d** on the planning lane).
- `inputs` (for the **planning child's** §5d spawn, not leader emit): `repoPath` / `outputs.hostingRoot`, existing `outputs.worktreePath` and `outputs.worktreeName` from debug child (worktree already created and modified), `developerApprovedImplementation: true`, `upstreamSkill: debug-and-fix`, required `targetPlanPath` and `targetPlanSlug` from step 5, plus `planningHandoffMode: "sections-1-4-complete"` and `planningHandoffApproved: true` when supplied by the **`pr-plan`** handoff; **ownership handoff (required with reuse):** `worktreeOwnership: "inherited"`, `worktreeCreatedByUpstream: "debug-and-fix"`, `mountedViaMcp: true` when the debug lane mounted the path (else `false` and **`coding-session`** may attach once without creating a new worktree); **`initiatingPrompt`** on that spawn must state ship starts at cut-point / commit, the §5 deploy-plan binding (Local test must **not** re-gate debug-verified manual scenarios), and that **inherited ownership authorizes post-merge auto-cleanup** on that exact path — **forbidden** to treat remount-only reuse as unclear ownership.
- `expected output`: Bubbled child terminals after ship chain milestones per **`coding-session`** **`## Completion (spawned)`** / inline ship skills (and/or planning-child aggregate after §5e).
- `next-step resolution`: Continue to step 7 after bubbled **`coding-session`** / planning terminal or when developer selects an external-wait resume option per skill gates (**#external-wait** while waiting).
- **Forbidden:** Squad Leader **`mission_control_spawn_agent`** for **`coding-session`** on this path.
- **Note:** Ship steps (commit, deploy-walk, pre-pr-review, create-pr, pr-review, post-merge cleanup, plan-reconcile) are **owned by `coding-session`** — do not duplicate procedure here. **`pre-pr-review`** spawn runs on a detached reviewer lane that auto-advances Steps **1–8** under Checkpoint trust — see **`pre-pr-review/SKILL.md`** § *Developer input vs external-wait (Checkpoint)*. **Debug upstream:** honor the PR plan §7 shape from §5 — do not invent Local test manual steps that re-run debug-session verification.
