### 6. Debug session findings report

- `type`: Finish/stop logic.
- `intent`: Summarize debug session outcomes when fix is **not** verified, **blocked**, or the developer chose **findings report only** at step 4.
- `inputs`: All child terminal outputs from step 3 (`fixSummary`, `testEvidence`, `fixStatus`, worktree paths), and any user decisions from step 4 when applicable.
- `expected output`: Structured findings recap in **`displayMarkdown`** — symptom, diagnosis, fix attempts, test evidence, **`### Worktree (copy-paste)`** with absolute **`worktreePath`** in a fenced code block (same shape as **`debug-and-fix/SKILL.md`** step **8**), and recommended follow-up. No downstream spawn.
- `next-step resolution`: Auto-advance step 7 when recap complete.
- `terminal vs resumable`: Resumable — dispatch remains active until step 7.

### 7. Dispatch resolution

USER_CHECKPOINT — approve dispatch resolution after findings report or code-promotion chain completes.

- `type`: Finish/stop logic.
- `intent`: Propose dispatch closure after findings report or code-promotion chain completes.
- `inputs`: All child terminal outputs, selected exit path, findings report from step 6 when applicable, any external-wait resume selection state.
- `expected output`: Squad Leader recap and **`mission_control_propose_dispatch_resolution`** when user signals done.
- `next-step resolution`: Terminal when user accepts resolution or continues from resolution card per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc) § *Dispatch resolution*.
- `terminal vs resumable`: **`resolved`** when code-promotion chain completed or findings report delivered; **`partial`** when fix verified but ship pending external action; **`aborted`** / **`abandoned`** on user stop or unrecoverable block.
